   HONG KONG -- Hong Kong's main measure of consumer prices
advanced 9.1% in June from a year earlier, the government
reported.
   For the 50% of urban households that spent between 2,000
and 6,499 Hong Kong dollars ($258 and $837) a month, consumer
prices rose 1% from May.
</LP>
