<TEXT>
   New York City -- $1.1 billion of general obligation tax
anticipation notes, Fiscal 1991 Series A, due June 28, 1991,
was won by eight underwriting groups, city officials
announced. The 6 1/4% notes, rated MIG-1 by Moody's Investors
Service Inc. and SP1-Plus by Standard &amp; Poor's Corp. will be
reoffered to yield 5.90%. The following groups won the deal:
Goldman, Sachs &amp; Co. and Carmona Ferrand Montes Securities
Corp., $675 million; Donaldson, Lufkin &amp; Jenrette Securities
Corp., $100 million; Lehman Brothers, $100 million; Bear,
Stearns &amp; Co., $50 million; First Boston Corp., $50 million;
Manufacturers Hanover Securities Corp., $50 million;
PaineWebber Inc., $50 million; First Albany Corp., $25
million. A total of 76 bids were placed from 24 firms, city
