water pollution control revenue bonds, 1990 Series A, due
March 1, 1993-2003, and 2012, with capital appreciation bonds
due 2004-2006, were tentatively priced by a Kidder, Peabody &amp;
Co. group to yield from 6.10% in 1993 to 7.15% in 2012.
Current interest serial bonds are priced at par to yield from
6.10% in 1993 to 6.95% in 2003. There are $22.8 million of
7.10% term bonds priced at 99.50 to yield 7.15% in 2012.
Capital appreciation bonds are priced to yield to maturity
from 7.05% in 2004 to 7.10% in 2005 and 2006. The bonds are
rated double-A-plus by S&amp;P.
   Alaska Energy Authority -- $61 million of power revenue
bonds, Bradley Lake Hydro Electric Project Issue, Second
Series, due July 1, 1992-2015, 2013 and 2021, with capital
appreciation bonds due 2006-2010, were tentatively priced by
a John Nuveen &amp; Co. group to yield from 6.10% in 1992 to
7.30% in 2021. Current interest serial bonds are priced at
par to yield from 6.10% in 1992 to 7.15% in 2005. There are
$7.5 million of term bonds priced at par to yield 7.20% in
2013. There are $29.8 million of 7 1/4% term bonds priced at
99 3/8 to yield 7.30% in 2021. Capital appreciation bonds are
priced to yield to maturity 7.10% in 2006-2010. The bonds are
insured and rated triple-A by Moody's and S&amp;P.
   Dade County, Fla. -- $55 million of aviation revenue
bonds, Series T, due Oct. 1, 1992-2005, were priced by a
Lazard Freres &amp; Co. group. The bonds are priced to yield from
6.15% in 1992 to 7.22% in 2005. There are no term bonds. The
bonds are insured and rated triple-A by Moody's and S&amp;P.
Interest on the bonds will be treated as a preference item in
calculating the federal alternative minimum tax that may be
imposed on certain investors.
   Richmond, Va. -- $50 million of general obligation revenue
anticipation notes, Series 1990 B, due June 28, 1991,
apparently were won by a Chemical Securities Inc. group. The
6 1/4% notes, rated MIG-1 by Moody's and SP1-Plus by S&amp;P,
were priced for reoffering to yield 5.90%.
   New Jersey Health Care Facilities Financing Authority --
$48.8 million of revenue bonds, Holy Name Hospital Issue,
Series B, due July 1, 1994-2004, 2010 and 2020, were
tentatively priced by a Dillon Read &amp; Co. group to yield from
6.10% in 1994 to 7.07% in 2020. Current interest serial bonds
are priced to yield from 6.10% in 1994 to 6.90% in 2004.
There are $10.8 million of 7% term bonds priced at 99 1/2 to
yield 7.05% in 2010. There are $18.1 million of 6 3/4% term
bonds priced at 96 to yield 7.07% in 2020. The bonds are
insured and rated triple-A by Moody's and S&amp;P.
                                                                                                       

                          MORTGAGE
                                                                                                       

   Rural Housing Trust 1987-1 (FHA) -- $540 million of
