   Business Brief -- CalMat Co.:
   Company Posts Lower Net
   For Quarter and 1st Half
</HL>
<DATE>
07/25/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   CZM
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
BUILDING MATERIALS (BLD)
DIVIDENDS (DIV)
</IN>
<LP>
   CalMat Co. reported lower second-quarter and first-half
earnings and said it expects 1990 earnings to be lower than
last year's $78.1 million, or $2.52 a share.
   The Los Angeles-based producer of construction materials
cited a decline in construction activity in many of its
market areas and a significant reduction for cement and
ready-mixed concrete in Southern California.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   In the quarter, net income fell 31% to $11.8 million, or
40 cents a share, from $17.1 million, or 55 cents a share, a
year earlier. Revenue declined 8% to $162.4 million from
$176.6 million. First-half net decreased 27% to $22.2
million, or 74 cents a share, from $30.3 million, or 98 cents
a share, a year earlier. Revenue slipped 5.6% to $310.6
million from $329.2 million.
   CalMat also declared a one-time dividend of 10 cents a
share payable Sept. 6 to stock of record on Aug. 10. It said
it declared the payout to fulfill a commitment.
