<HL>
   International Brief -- Oakbridge Ltd.:
   Elders Lifts Bid for Firm
   To Match Competing Offer
</HL>
<DATE>
07/25/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A9
</SO>
<CO>
   A.ELD A.OAK J.TMN J.NPO
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Elders Resources NZFP Ltd. raised its bid for Oakbridge
Ltd. to 88 Australian cents (69 U.S. cents) a share, matching
an offer made Monday.
   Australian coal miner McIlwraith McEacharn Ltd. is leading
a consortium with Toyo Menka Kaisha Ltd. and Nippon Oil Ltd.,
both of Japan, in a bid for control of Oakbridge, another
Australian coal company.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Elders is a New Zealand-based natural-resources company.
   The McIlwraith consortium is trying to pressure Elders to
sell it the 85% of Oakbridge that Elders holds.
   Elders said it raised its bid to 88 cents a share from 86
cents. That offer will be raised to 90 cents if Elders wins
90% of Oakbridge.
   John Cornelius, Elders secretary, said in a statement to
the Australian Stock Exchange that the McIlwraith bid is
"highly presumptuous." He added: "We are buyers of Oakbridge,
not sellers. Elders Resources has made no decision to sell
Oakbridge or any other assets for that matter."
</TEXT>
