<HL>
   Who's News:
   Amgen's Chief, Binder,
   Adds Chairman's Post
</HL>
<DATE>
07/25/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B6
</SO>
<CO>
   AMGN WNEWS
</CO>
<IN>
MEDICAL AND BIOTECHNOLOGY (MTC)
</IN>
<LP>
   THOUSAND OAKS, Calif. -- Gordon M. Binder, 54-year-old
chief executive officer of Amgen Inc., a biotechnology
company, was elected to the additional post of chairman,
succeeding George B. Rathmann.
   Mr. Rathmann, 62, was re-elected to the board and will
serve as chairman emeritus. A chemist, Mr. Rathmann joined
Amgen as president and chief executive in 1980, and was
elected chairman in 1986. In October 1988, he resigned as
president and chief executive but remained chairman.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   He said the election of Mr. Binder "completes the
transition in management that began two years ago."
